programme.sub-title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost

programme.series-desc: Two world wars tore the heart out of the twentieth century. Between these wars was an age that is viewed as a time of jazz, prohibition, the talkies, radio and the motor car. A time that, in reality, was an age of anxiety. A peace that failed.

programme.title: Crimes That Made History

programme.series-desc: Crimes and bloody tales that made the headlines usually reveal a lot about the hidden fantasies of their time. From Jack the Ripper to the Andes crash, the ten episodes of this collection shed a black light on a page of history that left a mark on time.

programme.desc: The Somme and Verdun saw carnage on an unprecedented scale, as armies fought to break the stalemate on the Western Front
programme.series-desc: This stunning account of WW1 offers new interpretations of and insights into one of the defining events of the twentieth century. It offers a truly global vision of a war that is so often misconceived as a prolonged skirmish on the Western Front.

programme.title: Weapons Race
programme.desc: For centuries men dreamed of machines which could win wars without slaughter on the ground. In today’s Northrop B-2A Spirit stealth bomber we seem to have reached this ideal.
programme.series-desc: Examine the development of new military technologies and how their evolution impacted tactics and strategies used in warfare from the High Middle Ages to the Modern Era.

programme.title: Battleplan
programme.desc: The Defensive Battle is often seen as the most dangerous of Battleplans as it allows the enemy to directly attack you and exhaust himself before you counterattack. Whatever the circumstances, this Battleplan requires great nerve and confidence
programme.series-desc: Examine the history of military tactics, from blitzkrieg to blockade, raiding operations to strategic bombing and on to guerrilla warfare.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.sub-title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Battles are almost always about territory. Advancing the front line, seizing the port, the city, the oil field. The fate of nations in the war rose and fell on battles that took territory. Singapore, Monte Casino, Stalingrad...all about territory.
programme.series-desc: Every battle is both a victory and a defeat; it depends which flag you fly. The battles of World War II were decided not only by strategy but by armies in their element. These battles won and lost would determine the course of the future.

programme.title: Copa do Caos
programme.desc: Os argentinos Pipo e Charly arrumaram as malas e estão no Brasil com um objetivo: assistir aos jogos da Copa do Mundo.

programme.title: Copa do Caos
programme.desc: Charly e Pipo encontram Neymar. E resolvem colocar em marcha um plano infalível: seqüestrar Neymar para ajudar a Argentina a vencer o Brasil. O tiro sai pela culatra e eles mudam de ideia: vão trocar Neymar por ingressos para a Copa.
programme.series-desc: Dois argentinos, Pipo e Charly, resolvem viajar de última hora ao Brasil para o Mundial de 2014.

programme.title: Copa do Caos

programme.series-desc: Dois argentinos, Pipo e Charly, resolvem viajar de última hora ao Brasil para o Mundial de 2014.

programme.title: Copa do Caos

programme.series-desc: Dois argentinos, Pipo e Charly, resolvem viajar de última hora ao Brasil para o Mundial de 2014.

programme.title: Copa do Caos
programme.desc: Charly e Pipo promovem uma luta na lama, já que com isso, poderão levantar fundos para ver a final no Rio. Só um aviso: cuidado com sua carteira ao assistir a esse episódio.
programme.series-desc: Dois argentinos, Pipo e Charly, resolvem viajar de última hora ao Brasil para o Mundial de 2014.

programme.title: Copa do Caos
programme.desc: Obstinação. Determinação. Garra. É disso que é feito qualquer grande time de futebol. E disso são feitos também Charly e Pipo. No dia do jogo da Argentina no Itaquerão, eles vão ter que dar um jeito de entrar no estádio, a qualquer custo.
programme.series-desc: Dois argentinos, Pipo e Charly, resolvem viajar de última hora ao Brasil para o Mundial de 2014.

programme.title: Copa do Caos
programme.desc: Na sua busca por ingressos, Charly e Pipo acabam achando muito mais: encontram aquilo que todo brasileiro gostaria de encontrar um dia: a Taça Jules Rimet. Entretanto, acabam se envolvendo com criminosos latinoamericanos.
programme.series-desc: Dois argentinos, Pipo e Charly, resolvem viajar de última hora ao Brasil para o Mundial de 2014.

programme.title: Copa do Caos
programme.desc: Uma perda irreparável. Doutor Cícero, o cearense que ajudava a Charly e Pipo partiu desta para melhor e, para complicar, levou junto com ele aquilo que a dupla mais queria: dois ingressos para a final do Mundial, pelos serviços prestados.
programme.series-desc: Dois argentinos, Pipo e Charly, resolvem viajar de última hora ao Brasil para o Mundial de 2014.

programme.series-desc: Dois argentinos, Pipo e Charly, resolvem viajar de última hora ao Brasil para o Mundial de 2014.
